Title: Ceiling modules in corten steel from building - Variable dimensions
Description: Geometric suspended ceiling in corten steel carefully dismantled by our team in the CCN Building by Groupe Structures (ca. 1974) in Gare du Nord, Brussels. Originally used as suspended ceiling, the modules seem to be perfect for other purposes such as night/coffee table or shelfs.Variable dimensions, only available in our shop.Steel sheet thickness : 0,2 cmUsed condition (B-quality). There are some scratches and imperfections (some parts have bolts or holes). Dusty, needs to be cleaned.
